The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Pope clarifies condom stand
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Pope clarifies condom stand
                            
	Vatican City, Nov. 23 (Reuters): Pope Benedicts landmark acknowledgement that the use of condoms is sometimes morally justifiable to stop AIDS is valid not only for gay male prostitutes but for heterosexuals and transsexuals too, the Vatican said today.        
	The clarification, the latest step in what is already seen as a significant shift in the Catholic Church policy, came at a news conference presenting the popes new book: Light of the World: The Pope, the Church, and the Sign of the Times.                                                                                                                                                          
